  <summary>3/7/2006--Introduced.
Justice for Crime Victims' Families Act - Requires the Attorney General to submit to the House and Sentate Judiciary Committees reports on measures to: (1) increase the success of federal, state, and local homicide investigations; and (2) improve the ability of federal, state, and local criminal investigators to solve homicides involving missing persons and unidentified human remains.</summary>
